commit.message:
Improve describe_categorical_1d() performance

A few changes have been done:

- Create variable `count_column_name`, rather than running `"count({c})".format(c=column)` again and again
- remove the usage of `f-string`. It's only supported from Python 3.6. This package is not using any special feature of Python 3.6+, so no point at all to break support to Python 2.7 and Python 3.4/3.5
- Much more efficient way to calculate `others_count` and `others_distinct_count`. According to my local simple testing, it reduces the time needed by more than half (~60 seconds -> ~25 seconds).

commit.message:
Optimize corr_matrix()

Correlation matrix has two important properties:
- it is a symmetric matrix
- the values on the diagonal are always 1.0

These two properties can help reduce the times of invoking .corr() from n^2 to (n^2-n)/2 (cut by more than half)

commit.message:
fix to ix which is deprecated 

the .ix formulation in pandas is deprecated and thus it has to be changed into .iloc or .loc. In this commit, I've solved this issue, in order to avoid warning messages at this moment and to avoid error messages in the future, when .ix is not allowed anymore in the future.
